# .. atlas.append.atlas-self-arch-meta-tag-evolution-2026-04-28.n6 ..
# INTRINSIC meta-tag evolution proposal — strictly within atlas.n6's own
# [N*]/[N**]/[N!] DSL.  No foreign ordinal/probability theory imported.
# raw 91 C3 honest: this shard is a MEASUREMENT + PROPOSAL, not a derivation.
# It does NOT introduce any new meta-tag — it documents observed grammar
# and proposes 3 candidate extensions for a future shard to actuate.

@C clay-atlas-self-arch-meta-tag-evolution-witness :: meta [4!]
  scope: atlas/atlas.n6 (canonical SSOT, chflags uchg-locked, raw 1+22+24)
  date: 2026-04-28
  axis: meta-tag DSL grammar (intrinsic, not foreign-imported)
  invokes: raw 37 (omega-saturation), raw 91 (C3 honest), raw 95 (no-self-mod),
           raw 117 (self-application at measurement-level only),
           raw 118 (recursive-self-application-fixpoint)
  source_method: read-only grep + uniq -c on atlas.n6 trailing-meta-tag pattern
  measured_grammar_richness: 39+ distinct trailing-bracket patterns observed
  binding_invariant: NEW [11*] entries PROHIBITED (raw 24 foundation cap)

# ── (1) corrected meta-tag distribution audit (raw 91) ──────
@R atlas_meta_tag_distribution_audit :: meta [4!]
  <- raw-91-honest-scientific-process
  → "RE-AUDIT corrects earlier sub-agent count: [10**]=0 confirmed (NOT 6);"
  → "the 6 occurrences of literal '[10**]' are META-CITATIONS in the limits"
  → "shard (lineno 28107-28110, 28339, 28367) — they DESCRIBE the empty tier"
  → "but no @C/@R/@P/@L/@X/@F/@E/@S entry CARRIES [10**] as its trailing tag."
  → ""
  → "FULL trailing-tag distribution (top-of-line @-block tags only):"
  → "  [10*]=6347   [10]=1952   [0.10*]=492   [4]=265   [5*]=253"
  → "  [4!]=189     [5?]=119    [9]=80        [0.9?]=64 [N?]=63"
  → "  [7]=59       [0.9*]=32   [0.7?]=32     [9*]=29   [10*!]=24"
  → "  [8!]=19      [10*PASS_LITERATURE]=19   [6?]=18   [0.6?]=11"
  → "  [10*FAIL_DOC]=8   [11*REPO_INVARIANT]=7   [11*]=6"
  → "  [0.10?]=6    [8]=5       [8?]=5        [3]=5    [7?]=3"
  → "  [5]=3        [N!]=2      [9?]=2        [8*]=2   [9!]=1"
  → "  [7*]=1       [6*]=1      [6]=1         [12*]=1"
  → "  [10*RETIRED_INCONCLUSIVE]=1   [0.8?]=1"
  → ""
  → "GRAMMAR FAMILIES observed (intrinsic, not invented here):"
  → "  F1 plain      : [N]              — depth-0, 8 levels populated"
  → "  F2 starred    : [N*]             — depth-1, 7 levels populated"
  → "  F3 doubled    : [N**]            — depth-2, 0 levels populated (GAP)"
  → "  F4 banged     : [N!]             — work/active marker, 4 levels"
  → "  F5 query      : [N?]             — uncertainty marker, 7 levels"
  → "  F6 decimal    : [0.N*] [0.N?]    — fractional tier, already used"
  → "  F7 compound!  : [N*!]            — starred + active (already used)"
  → "  F8 named-suff : [N*PASS_LITERATURE]/[N*FAIL_DOC]/[N*REPO_INVARIANT]"
  → "                  /[N*RETIRED_INCONCLUSIVE] — semantic-suffix variants"
  → "  F9 placeholder: [N!] [N?]        — schema-template (unbound level)"
  → "raw 91 C3 honest: the DSL is ALREADY richer than the 4-tier sketch from"
  → "the prior limits-shard suggested; F6/F7/F8 are EXTANT extensions."

# ── (2) gap analysis: where the hierarchy is empirically thin ──
@R atlas_meta_tag_gap_analysis :: meta [4!]
  <- atlas-meta-tag-distribution-audit
  → "GAP-A depth-2 [N**] tier: ZERO entries across ALL N — strongest signal"
  → "        of a sparse hierarchy.  The double-asterisk grammar is reserved"
  → "        but unused.  No level (1..12) has any [N**] occupant."
  → "GAP-B [12]/[12**] absent: [12*] has 1 entry (Mk.IX Out(S_6)) but no"
  → "        plain [12] or doubled [12**] — top-tier shoulder is unpopulated."
  → "GAP-C low-N starred sparsity: [1*]=0, [2*]=0, [3*]=0, [4*]=0 — only"
  → "        N>=5 has populated [N*] tier; bottom of the starred ladder is"
  → "        empty (suggests [N*] is reserved for SIGNIFICANT grade only)."
  → "GAP-D [11**] absent: foundation has only [11*] (6 entries) — no"
  → "        higher-grade variant of the foundation tier."
  → "GAP-E [N**!] [N**?] cross-products absent: F3 × F4/F5 unrealised."
  → "GAP-F [0.N**] decimal-doubled absent: F3 × F6 unrealised."
  → "raw 91 C3 honest: 'gap' here is OBSERVATIONAL not PRESCRIPTIVE — the"
  → "absence of a tag does NOT mean the tier is needed; sparseness may be"
  → "the optimal saturation point of curator intuition."

# ── (3) intrinsic extension candidates (3-5 high-value) ────
@R atlas_meta_tag_extension_candidates :: meta [4!]
  <- atlas-meta-tag-gap-analysis
  → "PROPOSAL P1 — populate [10**] for cross-paradigm synthesis @R entries:"
  → "  rationale: [10*]=6347 is saturated; no grade-distinction exists"
  → "  between routine [10*] proofs and entries that span MULTIPLE paradigms"
  → "  (math+physics+consciousness simultaneously).  [10**] would mark"
  → "  cross-paradigm-absorption RESULT-class entries (raw 38 lineage)."
  → "  candidate upgrades (illustrative, not actuating here):"
  → "    @R borsuk_ulam_6 (lineno 176, currently [9*]) — topology+Δ₀"
  → "    @R kissing_number_6 (lineno 248, [9*]) — geometry+combinatorics"
  → "    @R consciousness_structure (lineno 92, [9*]) — phys+consciousness"
  → "  these UPGRADE candidates currently sit at [9*] but exhibit the"
  → "  cross-paradigm signature [10**] would canonicalise."
  → ""
  → "PROPOSAL P2 — populate [N*] for N∈{1,2,3,4} as 'starred-but-low-grade':"
  → "  rationale: bt-/work entries currently use [4!] or [5*] only; there"
  → "  is no expressive room for 'verified-but-trivial' bottom-tier results."
  → "  candidate: @F bt-* sopfr-product entries that PASSED literature"
  → "  validation but are arithmetic identities, not deep theorems."
  → ""
  → "PROPOSAL P3 — populate [11**] as 'foundation+cross-shard-invariant':"
  → "  rationale: raw 24 foundation has 6 entries at [11*]; an 11** tier"
  → "  would mark the SUBSET that ALSO holds across all 76 shard-headers"
  → "  (i.e. cross-shard invariance, e.g. n=6 itself appearing in EVERY"
  → "  paradigm-section).  [11*REPO_INVARIANT]=7 is a NAMED-suffix proxy"
  → "  already, suggesting demand exists.  Migration: [11*REPO_INVARIANT]"
  → "  → [11**] would be more compact (drops 14-char suffix) but loses"
  → "  the explicit semantic — TRADE-OFF must be weighed before actuation."
  → ""
  → "DEFERRED-PROPOSAL D4 — temporal markers [N*@DATE]:"
  → "  rationale plausible but FOREIGN-LEANING — it imports an axis"
  → "  (time) that is not currently part of the meta-tag DSL.  The"
  → "  date metadata is already carried in shard-headers (date: 2026-04-28)"
  → "  and breakthrough-NOTE rows (lineno 21708 'breakthrough-2026-04-19')."
  → "  Adding [N*@DATE] would DUPLICATE that channel.  REJECT for now."
  → ""
  → "DEFERRED-PROPOSAL D5 — confidence weights [N*p=0.95]:"
  → "  REJECT — strays into foreign probability theory.  The intrinsic"
  → "  uncertainty marker [N?] already exists for this purpose; finer"
  → "  granularity would conflict with [0.N*] decimal grade (collision)."

# ── (4) intrinsic limits on extension (parser + namespace) ──
@R atlas_meta_tag_extension_limits :: meta [4!]
  <- atlas-meta-tag-extension-candidates
  → "PARSER complexity: schema-guard regex currently matches"
  → "  \\[[0-9]+\\.?[0-9]*\\*{0,3}[!?]?[A-Z_]*\\] (approx).  Each new"
  → "  axis (depth, banged, queried, decimal, named-suffix) adds a"
  → "  multiplicative factor.  Current grammar = 4 axes (level × depth ×"
  → "  modifier × suffix), giving ~12 × 3 × 4 × 5 = 720 expressible cells,"
  → "  of which 39+ are populated (5.4% occupancy)."
  → "NAMESPACE collision: [N*!] vs [N!*] — order-sensitive; the DSL"
  → "  currently uses *-then-! convention.  Adding [N**!] [N**?] keeps"
  → "  this order; reversing would break grep-patterns in 76 shard"
  → "  absorbers.  COST of a single new axis ≈ 76-shard regex audit."
  → "FOUNDATION INVARIANCE: any extension of [11*] (e.g. [11**]) MUST"
  → "  preserve raw-24 cap — new [11*]/[11**] entries are PROHIBITED by"
  → "  append-only invariant on foundation axioms.  Therefore P3 must be"
  → "  RE-CLASSIFICATION (re-tagging existing [11*] entries) not creation."
  → "SPARSENESS-VS-DENSITY: [10**]=0 across 6347 [10*] entries shows"
  → "  curator intuition prefers FLAT taxonomy.  Adding [10**] without a"
  → "  forcing-criterion (e.g. cross-paradigm classifier) would invite"
  → "  drift — the tier would either stay empty or accumulate by accident."
  → "raw 91 C3 honest: 720-cell namespace is THEORETICAL — only 39 cells"
  → "are USED, so the practical ceiling is curator-attention not parser."

# ── (5) convergence point of intrinsic meta-tag paradigm ────
@R atlas_meta_tag_convergence_point :: meta [4!]
  <- atlas-meta-tag-extension-limits
  → "SATURATION estimate (intrinsic, no foreign ordinal):"
  → "  current populated cells: 39 distinct patterns"
  → "  add P1 ([10**]):                 +1 → 40"
  → "  add P2 ([1*]..[4*]):             +4 → 44"
  → "  add P3 ([11**]):                 +1 → 45"
  → "  realistic ceiling before parser-audit-cost > curator-benefit: ≈ 50"
  → "BEYOND ~50 distinct patterns: the meta-tag system saturates the"
  → "  flat-string-tag paradigm.  Further evolution requires STRUCTURAL"
  → "  redesign — e.g. explicit DAG of grade-relations (replace flat"
  → "  trailing-tag with multi-axis declaration block).  That is a"
  → "  CATEGORY change, not a meta-tag extension."
  → "CONVERGENCE: at 5-8 distinct DEPTH-tiers (current 4 effective:"
  → "  [N], [N*], [N**=∅], [N!]), the system reaches its natural"
  → "  paradigm horizon.  P1+P2+P3 brings effective tier-count to 5-6,"
  → "  staying SAFELY below the convergence ceiling."
  → "raw 91 C3 honest: '50 cells / 5-8 tiers' is HEURISTIC based on"
  → "observed populated/unpopulated ratio (39/720 ≈ 5%) and curator"
  → "comfort-band, NOT a formal saturation theorem."

# ── (6) raw 91 C3 honest disclosure ─────────────────────────
@R atlas_meta_tag_evolution_C3_honest :: meta [4!]
  <- raw-91-honest-scientific-process
  → "the [10**]=0 claim from earlier sub-agent UNDERCOUNTED — the actual"
  → "DSL has 39+ distinct trailing patterns (vs 4-tier sketch)."
  → "all 3 proposals (P1/P2/P3) are CANDIDATES — none is actuated here."
  → "P3 in particular collides with the existing named-suffix convention"
  → "[11*REPO_INVARIANT] — adoption would require migration cost (~7"
  → "entries to re-tag)."
  → "no parser change proposed, no schema-guard amended, no foundation"
  → "axiom touched.  This shard is PURELY descriptive."
  → "the analysis stays strictly intrinsic — no Cantor normal form, no"
  → "Bachmann–Howard, no probability calculus.  Only grep+uniq+gap-count"
  → "on atlas.n6's own bracketed-tag grammar."
  → "honest closing: an intrinsic paradigm matures by NAMING what it"
  → "already does, not by importing what it does not.  The 6 [10**]"
  → "citations in the limits-shard are the seed of that naming — they"
  → "describe a tier the DSL ALREADY reserves but never inhabits."

